<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
This species is widespread in the West Indies, being described using material from Jamaica, Puerto Rico, and the Virgin Islands (Van Duzee 1927) and later reported from Dominica (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 141" refId="B67" refString="Robinson, H, 1975. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 185: 1 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" title="Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" volume="185" year="1975">Robinson 1975</bibRefCitation>
) and St. Lucia (
<bibRefCitation author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Studia dipterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="545 - 560" refId="B7" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2002. New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Studia dipterologica 9: 545 - 560" title="New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="9" year="2002">Bickel 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 141" refId="B67" refString="Robinson, H, 1975. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 185: 1 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" title="Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" volume="185" year="1975">Robinson (1975)</bibRefCitation>
described this species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robinson" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Condylostylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Condylostylus perpilosus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpilosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Condylostylus perpilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. albiciliatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="albiciliatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">C. albiciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Studia dipterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="545 - 560" refId="B7" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2002. New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Studia dipterologica 9: 545 - 560" title="New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="9" year="2002">Bickel (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. Adults of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. albiciliatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="albiciliatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">C. albiciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear to be active year-round on Montserrat.
</paragraph>
